\pard\b\f1\fs32 10  CHALLENGES FACED DURING DEVELOPMENT\par\par
\b0\f0\fs24 One major challenge was adapting the system from a role-divided dashboard model to a shared-access inventory model. Another challenge was balancing many operational controls in one page without creating a confusing interface. The products section, in particular, had to remain useful while supporting filters, creation, editing, and deletion.\par\par
A third challenge was cloud database deployment. Problems such as wrong hostnames, invalid passwords, SSL requirements, and incorrect database names repeatedly interrupted backend startup until the correct values were used. These problems were resolved through careful investigation and iterative correction.\par\par
These challenges improved the system overall because they forced clearer structure, stronger validation, and better deployment discipline.\par
\page
\pard\b\f1\fs32 11  SECURITY, VALIDATION, AND MAINTAINABILITY\par\par
\b0\f0\fs24 Security in this project is basic but important. Passwords are hashed before storage, and backend validation prevents invalid data from reaching the database. Required fields, numeric ranges, duplicate records, and stock violations are all checked server-side.\par\par
The codebase is maintainable because it is modular. Frontend logic is broken into focused components. Backend logic is split between routes, controllers, store functions, and utilities. This separation made later changes easier, including the shared-access behavior change.\par\par
Such maintainability is important in academic projects because it shows that the system can evolve rather than collapse when one requirement changes.\par
\page
\pard\b\f1\fs32 12  RESULTS AND OUTCOMES\par\par
\b0\f0\fs24 The project successfully delivered a working full-stack inventory platform with online deployment. It supports stock maintenance, supplier management, category management, purchases, sales, quantity editing, alerts, reorder logic, and dashboard reporting.\\par\\par
From a technical perspective, the project demonstrates frontend design, backend API development, SQL schema management, environment configuration, cloud deployment, and troubleshooting. From a business perspective, it gives the store a stronger way to understand stock and make better replenishment decisions.\\par\\par
The outcome is therefore both academically strong and practically meaningful.\\par
\page
